        &+rCHAPTER ONE: TUROLOPOLIS

        &+wThis tongue-twister of a town was founded in the year 62 by a
gentleman named Willem of Turol (Turol, of course, being the ancient
order of antipaladins to which Willem belonged). Willem had not yet
reached his thirtieth year, but had already acquired a great deal of
power, both within the order of Turol and in the environs around
Tharnadia. However, he found the growth of his dominion at a standstill
due to Tharnadia's long-standing ban on the slavery of sentient life.
Angered at these impositions, Willem set out to found his own city,
where he could possess people as well as things, and exercise his will
over them.
        Thus, over the relatively short span of eight decades did
Turolopolis grow into an impressively vast city. Indeed it was one of
the marvels of Duris in that its slave population greatly outnumbered
the freemen in the city. Even in the dark ages of long ago, no city
dared such a perilous position. Only the dark magic of Willem prevented
an uprising, and those few revolts that grew from infancy were cut down
by Willem's mighty guard, the Crimson Watch.
~
