chap2~
                &+WCHAPTER TWO: THE RING OF GLORY

        &+wIt was in the year 141 that the Ring of Glory, an accomplished
and well-respected guild based out of Woodseer, decided to take action
and free the slaves of Turolopolis. The six senior members of the Ring
formed ranks during the dead of the Month of Everfreeze, and set off.
An eyewitness to their arrival says that the fighting between the Ring
and the Crimson Watch was 'fiercer, more ferocious... than anything I
have seen before. Tiamat herself would have wilted beneath such an
onslaught.' The Ring of Glory, led by Kalmidor Spellforge, defeated
over forty Watchmen and provided enough time for over three hundred
slaves to make good their escape. However, in the end they were over-
whelmed and defeated. It is said, although I could not ascertain the
truth of this, that they were not immediately killed, that Willem had
something else in mind for them.
        This incident had two important effects outside of Turolopolis.
First, the Ring of Glory found itself without a vital core. Its six
most vital members had disappeared, and the guild disbanded soon
thereafter, drifting off to other guilds. Secondly, the already-frosty
relations between Turolopolis and Tharnadia degenerated even further,
and an outright war threatened.
~
