                &+rCHAPTER THREE: THE HOLOCAUST

        &+wAs Tharnadia was gearing up for a massive invasion of the city of
Turolopolis, the death of thousands was averted... by the death of thou-
sands. The following is a report by Volhar, a merchant who at that time
ran a wagon train from Myranthea to Turolopolis.

        &+c"Well, we was about a dozen leagues from the city gates, when
  ol' Kath pointed to a cloud that was fornimg up over the city. It
  wasn't like no cloud I'd seen before, either- it was a dark red
  color, like blood after it's been sitting awhile, almost black. I
  called to the wagons to halt, and we watched as this bright rain
  started fallin' out of the cloud. Even from that far I could see
  the little buildings go down like they was made of straw. I tell
  you, we were on our way back to Myranthea faster'n an Elf's arrow!
  I dunno what that cloud was, and I hope I never do."

        &+wThe author has conducted an extensive investigation of the
aforementioned cloud and has been unable to determine its origin. The
Board of Nobles in Tharnadia has disavowed any complicity, but one
cannot rule out the possibility that a team of sorcerors created such
a rain of fire and unleashed it on Turolopolis. It seems more likely,
however, that the gods themselves tired of Willem and his atrocities
and put an end to them in a most striking way.
